ostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Simon de Cotentin was born in 1089, in France, his father, William de Cotentin I, was 21 and his mother, Marianne D’Eu, was 19. He married Enid de Maatenloch in 1110, in Manche, Lower Normandy, France. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1136, in his hometown, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1089–1136":"1089–1136","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","1090–1130":"1090–1130","1110–1180":"1110–1180","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1068–1136":"1068–1136","1070–1140":"1070–1140","1090":"1090","1136":"1136","1068":"1068","1189":"1189","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","after 1130":"pärast 1130","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1070":"1070","1180":"1180","Cotentin, Lower Normandy, France":"Cotentin, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Coton, Shropshire, England":"Coton, Shropshire, England","France":"Prantsusmaa","Cotentin, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France":"Manche, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1089–1136":"1089–1136","1085–Male":"1085–Kuollut","1090–1130":"1090–1130","1110–1180":"1110–1180","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1068–1136":"1068–1136","1070–1140":"1070–1140","1090":"1090","1136":"1136","1068":"1068","1189":"1189","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","after 1130":"1130 jälkeen","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1070":"1070","1180":"1180","Cotentin, Lower Normandy, France":"Cotentin, Basse-Normandie, Ranska","Coton, Shropshire, England":"Coton, Shropshire, England","France":"Ranska","Cotentin, Manche, Basse-Normandie, France":"Manche, Basse-Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1089–1136":"1089–1136","1085–Male":"1085–Décédé","1090–1130":"1090–1130","1110–1180":"1110–1180","1130–1189":"1130–1189","1068–1136":"1068–1136","1070–1140":"1070–1140","1090":"1090","1136":"1136","1068":"1068","1189":"1189","1089":"1089","1110":"1110","after 11